---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../config';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header title={SITE_TITLE} />
		<main>
			
<p>
						I am currently working as a software engineer at <a href="https://www.yelp.com">Yelp</a> in London. Previously I was a software engineer at Kandra Labs (creators of <a href="https://zulipchat.com">Zulip</a> open source project). All the code I wrote
						while at Kandra Labs was open source and can be accessed <a href="https://github.com/zulip/zulip/commits?author=hackerkid">here</a>.
					</p>
					<h2 class="title is-4">
					Products
					</h2>
					<div class="projects-grid">
						<div class="project-tile">
							<h3><a href="https://diff.blog">diff.blog</a></h3>
							<div class="year">2019</div>
							<p>A platform to discover and follow amazing developer blogs.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="project-tile">
							<h3><a href="https://github.com/hackerkid/peerdium">Peerdium</a></h3>
							<div class="year">2018</div>
							<p>Decentralized P2P publishing platform built using browser cache and torrents.</p>
							<div class="project-badges">
								<span class="badge">Featured on <a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=17060272">HackerNews front page</a></span>
								<span class="badge"><a href="https://www.producthunt.com/posts/peerdium">#4</a> on ProductHunt</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="project-tile">
							<h3><a href="https://hackinthenorth.com">Hack In The North</a></h3>
							<div class="year">2016</div>
							<p>One of the largest student hackathons in India that I founded and organized.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="project-tile">
							<h3><a href="https://github.com/hackerkid/wikifeedia">Wikifeedia</a></h3>
							<div class="year">2015</div>
							<p>Newsfeed for Wikipedia that makes it easy to find and read interesting articles.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<h2 class="title is-4">
						Open source and community
						</h2>
						<ul>
							<li><a href="https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/archive/">Google Summer of Code</a> 2017 with Zulip.</li>
							<li>Mentor for Zulip in <a href="https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/archive/">Google Summer of Code</a> 2018, 2019 and 2020.</li>
							<li>Organization administrator for Zulip in <a href="https://codein.withgoogle.com/archive/">Google CodeIn</a> 2017.</li>
							<li>Mentor for Zulip in <a href="https://www.outreachy.org/">Outreachy</a> 2017.</li>
						</ul>
					<h2 class="title is-4">
					University
					</h2>
					<ul>
						<li>Bachelors in Information Technology (2013 - 2017) from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Institute_of_Information_Technology,_Allahabad">
							Indian Institute of Information Technology, Allahabad</a>.</li>
							<li>I was the overall coordinator of <a href="https://geekhaven.iiita.ac.in/">Geekhaven</a>, the organization
							responsible for running the technical activities in University. During this time (2015 - 2016) I managed the working of 7 sub divisions of
							the organization with over 14 coordintors and 40 members.
						</li>
						<li>
							I was in charge of events during the 2nd <a href="https://aparoksha.org/">Technical Fest</a> of University. I created,
							scheduled and coordinated over 25 events during the fest.
						</li>
					</ul>
					<h2 class="title is-4">
							Talks
						</h2>
						<ul>	
							<li>Building a profitable business around your open source project. (<a href="https://www21.in.tum.de/teaching/osp/WS20/index.html#vishnu-k.s.-how-to-build-a-profitable-business-around-your-open-source-project">TU Munich Open source course 2021</a> - <a href="https://github.com/hackerkid/talks/blob/master/pdf/building-a-profitable-business-around-your-open-source-project.pdf">Slides</a>)</li> 
							<li>What I learned from contributing to open source. (<a href="https://github.com/GeekHaven/quick_talks">GeekHaven GitHub QuickTalks 2017</a> - <a href="https://speakerdeck.com/hackerkid/what-i-learned-from-contributing-to-open-source">Slides</a>)</li>
							<li>The art of open source. (GDG Allahabad 2016 - <a href="https://speakerdeck.com/hackerkid/the-art-of-open-source">Slides</a>)</li>
						</ul>


		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.projects-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin: 2rem 0;
	}
	
	.project-tile {
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border: 1px solid rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
		backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
		transition: all 0.3s ease;
	}
	
	.project-tile:hover {
		border-color: #d97706;
		background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.1);
		transform: translateY(-4px);
		box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.2);
	}
	
	.project-tile h3 {
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
		font-size: 1.25rem;
	}
	
	.project-tile h3 a {
		color: #d97706;
		font-weight: bold;
	}
	
	.project-tile p {
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: #4a5568;
	}
	
	.project-badges {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.5rem;
	}
	
	.badge {
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
		background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.2);
		border-radius: 4px;
		color: #d97706;
		font-weight: 500;
	}
	
	.badge a {
		color: inherit;
	}
	
	.year {
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: #6b7280;
		font-weight: 500;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
	}
</style>
